{
  "id": 44202,
  "kuerzel": "M_IKAA",
  "bezeichnung": "Applied AI",
  "kreditpunkte": 2,
  "lernziele": "<p>The guiding idea is that AI is a powerful problem-solving&nbsp;tool and therefore every student needs to&nbsp;understand the fundamentals of AI to solve problems&nbsp;in their discipline. Hence, half of the module is used&nbsp;to teach the fundamentals of AI and the other half&nbsp;is used by the students to develop AI solutions to a&nbsp;problem from their discipline. In a novel hands-on&nbsp;didactic approach, AI fundamentals are made understandable&nbsp;to students who neither have had higher mathematics nor can program.</p>",
  "semesterBewertung": "bestanden / nicht bestanden",
  "sprache": "de-CH",
  "zustand": "aktiviert",
  "kurse": [
    {
      "id": 44203,
      "kuerzel": "IKAA",
      "bezeichnung": "Applied AI",
      "kreditpunkte": 0,
      "lernziele": "<p><strong>Sachkompetenzen </strong></p>\n<p>Die Studierenden k&ouml;nnen:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>explain why modern AI depends on Big Data and&nbsp;why AI is of fundamental importance</li>\n<li>explain why most interdisciplinary challenges can&nbsp;be addressed with AI and the resulting ethical&nbsp;implications</li>\n<li>explain the concept of probability intuitively and&nbsp;evaluate the performance of an AI algorithm</li>\n<li>distinguish between Supervised and Unsupervised&nbsp;Learning and between Regression and Classification</li>\n<li>identify AI applications from their</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Selbstkompetenzen </strong></p>\n<p>Die Studierenden k&ouml;nnen:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>reflect on how AI will change their discipline</li>\n<li>reflect on how AI will change society at large</li>\n<li>reflect on how AI will change their personal lives</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Sozialkompetenzen </strong></p>\n<p>Die Studierenden k&ouml;nnen:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>present their AI solutions and reflect on the&nbsp;different approaches and find the best solution&nbsp;together</li>\n<li>reflect on AI ethics and develop their own perspective which they then can defend in a group&nbsp;discussion</li>\n<li>present and argue for their own view on a pressing AI issue in a group discussion</li>\n</ul>",
      "planinhalt": "<p><strong>Lernblock I</strong></p>\n<p>Introduction</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What is AI &amp; why is AI important?</li>\n<li>Regression vs. Classification &amp; Supervised vs. Unsupervised &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lernblock II</strong></p>\n<p>Develop intuition</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Probability is fundamendal</li>\n<li>Develop intuition with tables</li>\n<li>Find your own AI problem in your discipline with the help of the teaching staff&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lernblock III</strong></p>\n<p>Supervised Learning</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Linear Regression</li>\n<li>k-Nearest Neighbors Classification</li>\n<li>Support Vector Machines</li>\n<li>Decision Trees &amp; Random Forests</li>\n<li>Neural Networks</li>\n<li>Language Models</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Lernblock IV</strong><br>Ethics and Examples</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Ethics and Examples</li>\n</ul>",
      "bibliographie": "",
      "empfLehrmittel": "<p>Inputreferate, Arbeiten in Teams an realen Problemstellungen, das Modul schafft Lernanl&auml;sse, aktive Mitarbeit steht im Vordergrund.</p>",
      "bemerkungKurs": "",
      "leistungsnachweis": "<p>Aktive Pr&auml;senz, Prozess-Dokumentation, Pr&auml;sentationen.</p>",
